A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Food and Milk Product Labeling – Requirements
3 FOR the purpose of requiring, beginning on a certain date, certain food manufacturers,
4 processors, and retailers to use certain terms regarding the quality or safety date on
5 labels of food items manufactured for human consumption; prohibiting, beginning on
6 a certain date, a person from selling, or offering for sale, food items manufactured
7 for human consumption that are labeled with a “sell by date” or that do not meet the
8 labeling requirements of certain provisions of this Act; requiring the Maryland
9 Department of Health to create a marketing program and educational materials for
10 food labels on or before a certain date and to post the information on the
11 Department’s website; requiring that certain milk products be labeled with a certain
12 quality assurance date; and generally relating to food and milk product labeling
13 requirements.
